SIMPLE: homologue
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Homologue
<hw>Hom"o*logue</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>homologue</ets>. See <er>Homologous</er>.]</ety> <def>That which is
homologous to something else; <as>as, the corresponding sides, etc., of
similar polygons are the <ex>homologues</ex> of each other; the members
or terms of an homologous series in chemistry are the
<ex>homologues</ex> of each other; one of the bones in the hand of man
is the <ex>homologue</ex> of that in the paddle of a
whale.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Homology</ent>⟦br⟧
